SQLite Integration:
  - MSG_QUEUE table for telemetry events
  - SESSION table for sessions
  - how do we handle:
    - login (userId)
    - sessions
    - telemetry


API calls:
- config
   - happens on connect()
   - NO sql required
- login
   - requires username and password (gathered in menus)
   - receive back courseId and clientId
   - NO sql required
   - does it require flush ???
- logout
   - no data
   - NO sql required
- start session
   - requires courseId and gameLevel -- [login]
   - receive back gameSessionId
   - SQL required
- end session
   - SQL required
- send telemetry
   - requires gameSessionId -- [start session]
   - SQL required


SQLite tables:
- SESSION
   - [cookie | deviceId]
- MSG_QUEUE
   - [deviceId | path | coreCB | clientCB | postdata | contentType]



